  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mushroom culture for refugees in Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Uganda refugees live a life of poverty, without employment,without hope while they have talents in different fields,such as agriculture of mushrooms.With this project,we have assurance that 80% of 25,516 elderly refugees living in Uganda (20,412)will have access to nutrition and education.This project will change the lives of refugees. Each elder&apos;s refugee household will receive an important quantity of mushroom which will help him to feed the family need and the school fees for his children.</narrative>
  </description>
